The paper discusses a novel approach to software engineering based on the SP Theory of Intelligence, which is a theory of general intelligence that has been applied to various areas of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the automation or semi-automation of software development, which is a key topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for reductions in the number of computer languages and the elimination of the distinction between program and database, which are topics related to programming languages (cs.PL) and databases (cs.DB).
